               <msContents>
                  <summary/>

                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <locus from="1ra" to="76vb"/>
                     <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2342serata">The Order of the Monastic Profession of St Anthony Given to him by God</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                     
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                        <locus target="#1r"/><hi rend="rubric">በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="DN"/></hi> ሥርዓተ፡ መ<hi rend="rubric">ንኵስና፡ ዘአቡነ፡</hi><persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1962Anthony">Antony<sic resp="DN">እንጦስ፡</sic></persName> ዘወሀቦ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ሶበ፡ ሰአለ፡ ኀቤሁ። 
                        ይቤ፡ ዘፈቀደ፡ ይልበስ፡ ምንኵስና፡ ቅዱስ፡ ይነብር፡ ማእከለ፡ መነኮሳት፡ ፩ዓመ<cb n="b"/><hi rend="rubric">ተ፡ አው፡ ፫ዓመተ፡ እንዘ፡ ይትመ</hi>ከር፡ ወይትለአክ፡ 
                        ወይፍትንዎ፡ <hi rend="rubric">በኵሉ፡ ግብሩ፡ ለ</hi>ይኅድግ፡ እከዮ፡ ወይትሌለይ፡ እምግብሩ፡ ዓለም፡ ወአንሰሰዎ፡ እም፡ ኮነ፡ ርቱዓ፡ በኵሉ፡ ሠናይ፡ 
                     </incipit>                     
                     <explicit xml:lang="gez">
                        <locus target="#76va"/>ነጽረኒ፡ ወስምዓኒ፡ እግዚኦ፡ አምላኪየ፡ <cb n="b"/> 
                        አብርሆን፡ ለአዕንትየ፡ ከመ፡ ኢይኑማ፡ ለመዊት፨
                        <hi rend="rubric">ወእዜም<gap reason="illegible" unit="chars" quantity="2"/></hi> ለስመ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ልዑል፡ <hi rend="rubric">እባርክ፡</hi>
                        ለእግዚአብሔር፡ በኩሉ፡ ጊዜ። ቅረቡ፡ ኀቤሁ፡ ወያብርህ፡ ለክሙ፡ ጣዕሙ፡ ወታእምሩ፡ ከመ፡ ኄር፡ እግዚአብሔር፨ 
                     </explicit>
                     <note>The text seems to be similar to the Monastic Ritual as preserved in such manuscripts as 
                        <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/Tanasee154">Samen Gondar, Dāgā ʾƎsṭifānos, Ṭānāsee 154</ref>,  <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/Tanasee81">Tanasee81</ref>, 
                        <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESam12">ESam12</ref>, <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/EMML233">Collegeville, Hill Museum and Manuscript Library, MS EMML no. 233</ref>, but here
                        it is modified in the beginning through the
                        introduction of the figure of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1962Anthony">Anthony the Great</persName> as the receptor.</note>
                  </msItem>


